  <p align="left"><strong>MLT UPDATE</strong></p>
  <p align="left">Shalom ||usefirstname||</p>
  <p align="left"> You gotta love updates&hellip; don&rsquo;t worry this will be short and to the point. We feel in the mood for some Strategic Action Bullet Points. So here we go&hellip;</p>
  <ul>
    <li> It is with great excitement that we can tell you that Hannah Bruce (all the way from the mighty Timaru) has been appointed to the Leadership Team of Incedo. Hannah brings a fresh perspective, to the team and also to the three boys. She is the right person to come onto the team, and Hannah feels it is also the right time. This is an exciting step for us as a community, as well as for Hannah.<br>
    </li>
    <li> We spent last weekend with a few &ldquo;New Schoolers&rdquo; down in Christchurch (big ups to Tracy for the fantastic/historic/slightly creepy at night house). This was a great time of laughter, prayer, reflection, Val Kilmer, dreaming, talking, food, and looking forward. We are privileged to have in Incedo, a group of people who are willing to take a lead/dream/love/challenge/ in different areas of the Incedo community. We have already seen this in action with the email Andy sent out on Monday, and there are other plans in the pipeline. <br>
    </li>
    <li> There is a good history of people coming from different parts of the world to spend time serving with us here in NZ. As we evolved as Incedo, we have realised that we need to revisit how the process works. This is not a reflection on how we have done it, but we do need to tighten up the process so that it is beneficial for all people involved. As was mentioned at The Gathering last year, The MLT must approve any application from anyone wishing to spend time in NZ serving with Incedo- this ensures that they fully understand how we &ldquo;operate&rdquo;, and what we expect from them. Anyone spending time here will be expected to operate as a member, and will received updates, and the 3x3x3. Any applications to spend time in NZ must be made to the MLT, its not that we wish to exert any control, we simply want to have a uniform practice in place.<br>
    </li>
    <li> Big thanks and much respect to the following: Kelly- for the classy, thought provoking, and sometimes odd videos that grace the Incedo page on a Monday; Greg- for all the computer interweb stuff, the members page, and sending out the updates; Mike W- for ensuring we get the 3x3x3 bible verses; Glen &ndash; for the prayer updates; Gus, Tracy, and Blair- for serving us on the board; Bryan and Rochelle- for all they do so that we don&rsquo;t get into trouble over $$; All those who comment on the forum- they keep our brains active. <br>
    </li>
    <li> Lastly, thanks for taking the time to read this update.</li>
  </ul>  
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>Karl, Glen, Hannah, Paul<br>
    (<a href="mailto:mlt@incedo.org.nz">mlt@incedo.org.nz</a>) <br>
  </p>
