  <p><strong>DAILY PRAYERS</strong><br>
    <br>
    Over the last couple of years, we have explored the idea of a daily recited prayer as one small way of expressing unity across Incedo. The idea is that if, on any particular day, you are meeting with other Incedo people, you say that days prayer together. If you're on your own, you pray the prayer in solidarity with Incedo members nationwide.<br>
    <br>
      Here's 5 prayers for 2009<br>
      <br>
      <strong>Monday</strong> (Joy Cowley)<br>
      <br>
      Jesus<br>
      You are the Way<br>
      The bridge between Heaven and Earth<br>
      between the smallness of self<br>
      and the greatness of God<br>
      You are the path we choose to follow<br>
      and can never lose,<br>
      because it resides in our hearts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Amen.</p>
  <p> <strong>Tuesday</strong> (adapted from Ruth Graham)<br>
        <br>
        God of the Universe<br>
        Whose Son endured death<br>
        and defied death<br>
        We find our leaden spirits<br>
        lifted from the dust<br>
        confident that You,<br>
        who has brought us so far<br>
        on Your way<br>
        will see us through.</p>
  <p> <strong>Wednesday</strong> (from Theodotus, AD 304)<br>
          <br>
          Lord Jesus<br>
          Creator of Heaven and Earth<br>
          you will never abandon us<br>
          you are preparing us to live in your kingdom<br>
          you are strengthening us to overcome<br>
        and we give you thanks</p>
  <p> <strong>Thursday</strong> (adapted from Walter Bruggemann)<br>
          <br>
          Lord<br>
          push us beyond ourselves<br>
          in <u>wonder</u> at your ways<br>
          in <u>love</u> for the world you love<br>
          in <u>praise</u> that transforms our fears<br>
          push us beyond ourselves<br>
        towards you.</p>
  <p> <strong>Friday</strong> (adapted from Dietrich Bonhoeffer)<br>
          <br>
          Jesus<br>
          In us there may be darkness<br>
          but in you there is light<br>
          we may be lonely<br>
          but you do not leave us<br>
          weak in spirit<br>
          but with you there is hope<br>
          restless<br>
          but in you there is peace<br>
          we may not understand<br>
          but you know the way<br>
        Enable us to live in you.</p>
